args: Damn. We're good and lost now.
In that case, let's set up camp here\nbefore the sun goes down.
Right. I'll go track down some firewood.
Ooo! I haven't been camping in forever!
You were traveling and hunting\nbefore you came to us, right?

Yep! Then I camped every day, which was
great. I'm still not used to the beds you
have in the castle—they're so soft
and scratchy and...blech!
I fear I have some bad news regarding\nour current provisions...
...So we're running low on water?\nThat's gonna make things tight.
We also lack a tent or any other shelter.
Nya ha ha! That's no problem at all!
I'll teach you how to set up a camp like\nmy tribe does. We'll do it hunter-style!
We need to dig a hole big enough for\nthe four of us, then fill it with grass.
Then we poke a few tree branches into the\nground and hang cloth from them like so...
Ta-daaa! One tent, ready for a pack\nof intrepid campers!
No time to stand around gawking at my\nawesomeness! Night's gonna fall soon.
Aaaand soooo... Ah, there we go.
Er, why are you pulling all the vines\nfrom that tree? Do we need rope?
Nope! See, this tree accumulates water.
And if you cut the vines and stick them in\nthe mouth of your canteen like so...
That's the idea! C'mon, let's fill up\nthe remaining canteens.
I'm back with enough firewood to\nroast a pig! ...Not that we got one.
Thanks, Ranzal. We've just finished up\nour preparations as well.
Saaay! For bein' an improvised campsite,\nthis place looks plenty comfy.
Indeed. We should have no problems\nmaking it through the night now.
And it's all thanks to Yue.
Nya ha ha! More praise! More, I say!
Enough chatter—let's get a fire goin'\nbefore my toes freeze off!
How do you have such a working\nknowledge of nature, Yue?
I was wondering the same thing.\nDoes every member of your tribe know\nthese skills, or are you a special case?
Oh, we all know SOME survival skills,\nbut my family was always the best at it.
We'd always roam the farthest and seek\nout the most dangerous game.
Sometimes we'd be gone for days or\neven weeks, so knowing how to camp\nwas a huge priority.
Sounds like your family was the most\nformidable of an already formidable\ngroup of people.
Yeah, my parents were both amazing.\n*sniff* I still miss 'em a bunch.
Miss them as in homesick?\nOr miss them as in...
They were attacked by an entire herd\nof angry beasts a little while back.
It IS terrible. I'm so sorry, Yue.
I don't think it's terrible, actually.
My people hunt. And if you hunt, of course\nyou sometimes also get hunted.
So while I do MISS them terribly,\nI also understand why things\nare how they are.
My parents are one with the land now.
And that's why, so long as I live here on\nthis earth, I'll never be alone!
Yer really somethin', kid. Ya know that?\nI dunno if I've ever met anyone who has\nthat kind of strength.
Here we were thinkin' yer life story\nwas this grim tragedy! But I guess\nit's all about perspective, eh?
Your tribe's connection with\nthe land would make its people\nquite strong indeed.
But it's not just your parents who are\nwith you, Yue—we are as well.
*yawn* All this talking has me bushed!\nI'm gonna go get some shut-eye.
You all get some sleep too, okay?\nRest is important in a survival situation.
Yue's as tough as they come, but she\nstill looks like a little kid when she's\nall conked out like that.
One could easily mistake her for a\nguileless, innocent child.
And yet she's lived a life most of us\nwill never understand.
